<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 92-08-13 - Delco 21SI Alternator Ignition Turn-On</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi920813" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>92-08-13</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>November, 1992</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ELECTRICAL</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Delco 21SI Alternator Ignition Turn-On</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Delco</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>1000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>2000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>3000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>5000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8300</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>TSI-91-08-04, dated July 1991, describes the need to rev the engine in some instances to cause the
                    Delco 21SI alternator to begin charging. Effective in the Spring, 1992, all Navistar engines have
                    two-wire ignition turn-on Delco 21SI alternators as standard. These alternators will begin charging
                    as soon as the engine starts, without the need to rev the engine. One-wire Delco 21SI alternators
                    can be converted to the two-wire ignition turn-on type if the alternator is equipped with an
                    existing square "I" terminal hole in the rear housing. Use the following procedure to install an
                    ignition turn-on wire.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install Kit Part Number 10479701 (purchased from Delco) as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9208131">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a 14 or 16 gauge wire from the
                    <emph type="bold">accessory</emph>
                    side of the ignition switch to the "I" terminal of the alternator. A rectifier/diode Part Number
                    1986924 (purchased from Delco) must be installed in this wire with the silver band toward the
                    alternator "I" terminal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If resistance wire circuit #1 exists in the vehicle harness, it can be used in lieu of the
                        rectifier (diode).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f9208131" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9208131.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. "I" Terminal Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A. DELCO KIT #10479701</callout1>
                    <callout1>1. REGULATOR STUD NUT AND WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. INSIDE "BAT" TERM. NUT AND WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. "I" TERMINAL CONN.</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. INSIDE "I" TERMINAL NUT AND WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. INSIDE INSULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. "I" TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. "BAT" TERMINAL STUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. REGULATOR STUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. REGULATOR STUD CONN.</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
